│ predicates to unsigned if `isKnownNonNegative` for both operands. In our │
│ case, this flip is unsafe because the non-negativity of `%mul2` is not   │
│ guaranteed under `%x < 0` (the term (%x+5001000) can be                  │
│ negative/zero/positive), so `%mul2` can be <= 0.\n\n3. Root Cause        │
│ Analysis:\n`ConstraintInfo::getConstraintForSolving` currently converts  │
│ signed predicates to unsigned purely based on ValueTracking's            │
│ `isKnownNonNegative(OpX, DL, ...)` for both operands, without            │
│ considering the current constraint system (facts from assumes/branches). │
│ This global analysis can claim `%mul2` is non-negative due to nsw flags  │
│ and multiplication patterns, even if under current constraints it isn't  │
│ guaranteed. As a result, the predicate is flipped to unsigned,           │
│ strengthening it and enabling an incorrect implication proof.\n\nWe have │
│ evidence in code that elsewhere the pass uses a more robust check        │
│ combining Info and ValueTracking: in `transferToOtherSystem`,            │
│ `IsKnownNonNegative` is defined as `doesHold(SGE, V, 0) ||               │
│ isKnownNonNegative(V, DL, ...)`. In contrast, `getConstraintForSolving`  │
│ only uses `isKnownNonNegative` for both operands without Info-based      │
│ reasoning. This discrepancy can cause incorrect signed->unsigned         │
│ flipping before decomposition/solving.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\nWe │
│ should modify `ConstraintInfo::getConstraintForSolving` to require that  │
│ non-negativity be established in the current constraint context using    │
│ `doesHold(ICMP_SGE, V, 0)` instead of relying solely on ValueTracking.   │
│ Optionally, we can keep the ValueTracking as a secondary heuristic but   │
│ prioritize Info-based proof.\n\nEdit details:\n- File:                   │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/ConstraintElimination.cpp\n- Lines: 782-809   │
│ (the body of getConstraintForSolving)\n\nChange the signed->unsigned     │
│ flip from:\n```\n// If both operands are known to be non-negative,       │
